Package: SpatialDataR
Title: Native R Interface to the SpatialData Zarr Format for Spatial
    Omics
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R:
    person("Cuiwei", "Gao", email = "48gaocuiwei@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides native R infrastructure for reading
    SpatialData-formatted Zarr stores (Marconato et al. 2024,
    <doi:10.1038/s41592-024-02212-x>) without Python dependencies.
    Discovers and reads images, labels, points, shapes, and
    annotation tables from '.zarr' directories following the
    OME-NGFF specification (Moore et al. 2023,
    <doi:10.1007/s00418-023-02209-1>). Supports Zarr array reading
    (via 'Rarr' or 'pizzarr'), Parquet and CSV tabular data
    (via 'arrow'), affine coordinate transformations with
    composition and 3D support, bounding box spatial queries,
    and coercion to 'SpatialExperiment'. Designed as a bridge
    between the Python 'SpatialData' ecosystem and
    R/Bioconductor spatial analysis workflows.
License: Artistic-2.0
